dc_description_s: This data represents addresses for Taylor County, WIsconsin in 2021. [This data set consists of digital map files containing addressing or site access information obtained by lab work. Features contained in the data set include all site access points countywide and associated attributes. Features contained in the data set include all site access points countywide and associated attributes. Site access points sometimes are referred to as addresses, however these data typically represent the intersection of the public road right of way and the private entrance to the property. In urban areas the site access is represented at the located where the primary structure is perpendicular to the public road right of way. The Taylor County Land Information Office plans to maintain this digital data in geodatabase format in an ESRI ArcSDE environment using ArcMap tools.]
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. [This data set was created as a foundational element for the Taylor County Land Information System. The site access feature class provides a digital representation of all addresses or site access points within Taylor County and is to be used in conjunction with developed digital road centerline, building, and driveway feature classes. The site access feature class was intended to be used to enhance addressing information within the County.]
